Product Requirements Document (PRD)
Project Name
ResQMesh
Tagline

“When networks fail, people become the network.”

1. Executive Summary

ResQMesh is an AI-powered offline-first emergency communication platform designed for disaster situations where traditional internet and cellular infrastructure fails.

The platform enables users to:

send SOS alerts without internet,
relay emergency messages through nearby devices,
locate safe zones,
connect with volunteers,
share resources,
and help rescue teams prioritize emergencies using AI.

ResQMesh combines:

peer-to-peer mesh communication concepts,
AI emergency classification,
volunteer coordination,
offline accessibility,
and disaster-response visualization

into one unified emergency response ecosystem.

The hackathon MVP demonstrates how nearby smartphones can act as communication relay nodes during disasters.

2. Problem Statement

During disasters such as:

floods,
earthquakes,
landslides,
wildfires,
riots,
stampedes,
train accidents,
network blackouts,

internet and telecom infrastructure often become unavailable.

As a result:

victims cannot request help,
rescue teams lack visibility,
emergency response becomes delayed,
local resources remain uncoordinated,
and critical lives are lost.

Existing emergency applications heavily rely on internet connectivity and centralized infrastructure, making them unreliable exactly when they are needed most.

3. Vision Statement

To create a resilient decentralized emergency communication ecosystem where nearby devices collaborate to keep communication alive during disasters, ensuring faster rescue coordination and saving lives even without internet connectivity.

4. Goals
Primary Goals
Enable offline SOS communication.
Prioritize emergencies using AI.
Coordinate rescue efforts efficiently.
Improve disaster response visibility.
Build an accessible emergency ecosystem.
Secondary Goals
Resource sharing.
Volunteer coordination.
Safe-zone discovery.
Community-powered communication.
