8. Functional Requirements
8.1 SOS Alert System
Description

Allows users to send emergency alerts.

Features
One-tap SOS button
Emergency categories
Voice/text input
Auto location
Battery metadata
Timestamp
User identification
Emergency Types
Medical
Fire
Flood
Violence
Trapped
Food/Water
Shelter
Missing Person
Inputs
Field	Type
Emergency Type	Dropdown
Message	Text
Voice Input	Audio
Location	Auto
Battery %	Auto
Outputs

Structured SOS object.

8.2 Offline Relay Layer
Description

Messages are relayed through nearby devices.

MVP Behavior

Simulated nearby node relay.

Future Behavior

Bluetooth/WiFi Direct mesh communication.

Message Metadata
Field	Description
Alert ID	Unique identifier
Hop Count	Relay count
TTL	Expiry
Sender ID	Origin
Timestamp	Creation time
Status	Sent/Relayed/Uploaded
8.3 AI Emergency Classification
Description

AI analyzes incoming emergency messages.

AI Tasks
classify category
detect severity
assign priority
summarize message
suggest action
detect fake/spam alerts
Severity Levels
Low
Medium
High
Critical
Example Output
{
  "category": "Medical",
  "severity": "Critical",
  "priorityScore": 96,
  "summary": "Person unconscious and needs urgent medical support.",
  "suggestedAction": "Dispatch ambulance immediately"
}
